wmcpuwatch (dockapp that shows CPU load)

wmcpuwatch is a WindowMaker dockapp which aims to show the load of
every logical CPU on the system.

It is a fork of wmmon. wmmon shows the load of up to 10 CPUs. With
a little tweaking it is possible to show 12 with wmmon, but when in
2017 Intel announced an 18 core CPU (and AMD was with their Ryzen even
earlier), then it was time for a new dockapp.

wmcpuwatch now shows the load of all CPUs in the lower frame which
allows up to 40 CPUs max.
